* {{audio|en|en-us-crime.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|en|aɪm}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|~}}

# {{lb|en|countable}} A [[specific]] [[act#Noun|act]] [[commit]]ted in [[violation]] of the [[law]].
# {{lb|en|countable}} Any [[great]] [[sin#Noun|sin]] or [[wickedness]]; [[iniquity]].
#* {{RQ:Pope Cecilia|passage=No '''crime''' was thine, if 'tis no '''crime''' to love.}}
# {{lb|en|countable|obsolete}} That which [[occasion#Verb|occasions]] crime.
#* {{RQ:Spenser Faerie Queene|book=I|canto=IX|stanza=46|passage=the tree of life, the '''crime''' of our first father's fall}}
# {{lb|en|uncountable}} [[criminal#Adjective|Criminal]] acts [[collectively]].
#: {{synonyms|en|criminality|delinquency}}
# {{lb|en|uncountable}} The [[habit]] or [[practice#Noun|practice]] of committing crimes.
#: {{ux|en|'''Crime''' doesn’t pay.}}

